/* Sound clips */ NO.
/* Sound clips */ no
/* Easy listening singers */ can't imagine why this has gone over two years without a cite. Besides the fact that it's overgeneralizing idiotic bullshit, I mean
/* History */ was this written fifty years ago? not cited, and not remotely true according to the FM station listings of any current Western market
oy
/* Theories */ a section for theories would be useful, but this is just three paragraphs of Molyneux, starry-eyed as always, hyping his video game in Wikipedia's voice.
/* Creative solutions */ so, basically using the dev's PR uncritically to support a somewhat dubious claim (given simplistic mechanics of the game's engine)
/* Notable artists */ evidently not so
over 200? Cite or gtfo, even the MobyGames is well under 200, and that includes "sound driver by ___" sort of non-composer credits
/* Web Series */ non-notable fanfiction written in an off-putting, fawning promotional tone, references are a youtube video and the project's own website
/* Plot */ might as well wikilink "two" while you're at it
/* Documentary */ doesn't need wikilink
/* Music box sets */ random burbling that bears no logical relation to the sentence immediately preceeding it
/* Production */ what scant few words of this paragraph that weren't stupefyingly trite (wow, a movie used... cameras!?) were completely unsourced (and still pretty trite)
/* Cultural phenomena */ we don't need the heavy-handed moralizing
/* Trial */ durrrrrrrrr thanks for restating the previous sentence thanks so much!! thanks. thank you
/* Eclipse bankruptcy */ durrrrrrrrr thanks for restating the previous sentence thanks so much!! thanks
